==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ribibe
<hw>Rib"ibe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Rebec</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sort of stringed instrument; a
rebec.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An old woman; -- in contempt.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A bawd; a prostitute.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ribible</ent>⟦br⟧
